title: A Walk in the Park: Learning to Walk in 20 Minutes With Model-Free Reinforcement Learning

definitions.Model-Free Reinforcement Learning: A type of reinforcement learning that does not use a model of the environment to make decisions.

formulas: Q-learning formula: Q(s, a) = Q(s, a) + \alpha [R + \gamma \max_a Q(s', a) - Q(s, a)]
summary: The slide presents a study on learning to walk in 20 minutes using model-free reinforcement learning. It includes a Q-learning formula and keywords related to the topic.
